  "prompt": "How often should one visit a dentist?",
  "response": "Most dental professionals recommend visiting the dentist for a routine check-up and cleaning at least twice a year, or every six months. However, the frequency can vary based on individual needs. Some people may require more frequent visits if they have specific dental health issues, such as gum disease or a high risk of cavities. Others with good dental health may be fine with annual visits. It's best to consult your dentist to determine the right schedule for your dental care.",
